<br>
==Annotations==
'''''primafacie'''''{{spaces|5}}(''Latin'') ''[[wikt:prima facie|prima facie]]'' is a Latin expression meaning ''at first sight'', ''on the face of it''. In English it may be used as an adjective meaning ''obvious'', ''not requiring proof''. Hans Walter Gabler amended Joyce's ''primafacie'' to ''prima facie''.<ref>{{cite book |title=Ulysses: The Corrected Text |last=Joyce |first=James |editor=Hans Walter Gabler |others=With Wolfhard Steppe and Claus Melchior |year=1986 |publisher=The Bodley Head |location=London |page=336}}</ref>

