[[File:Ulysses, 1922.djvu|thumb|600px|center|page=416]]
<br>
==Annotations==
'''''Aurora borealis'''''{{spaces|5}}(''Latin'') ''Northern dawn'', the scientific name for the [[w:Aurora_(astronomy)|Northern Lights]]. Bloom imagines that the light he can see is an aurora, but he is looking south! See also [[Annotations_to_James_Joyce's_Ulysses/Circe/452|452.21]].

