==Annotations==
'''''Dona nobis pacem'''''{{spaces|5}}(''Latin'') ''Grant us peace''.<ref>Gifford (1988) 511.<br>Thornton (1968) 410.</ref> This is the concluding phrase of the ''[[w:Agnus Dei (liturgy)|Agnus Dei]]'' (''Lamb of God''), which is sung in the [[w:Tridentine Mass|Latin Tridentine Mass]] during the [[w:Mass (liturgy)|Communion Rite]]. Lynch is completing Stephen's parody two lines before.

