==Annotations==
'''''post mortem'' child'''{{spaces|5}} ''Post mortem'' is Latin for ''after death''. Bloom is using the phrase attributively to describe a child born after the death of its father; in this case, of course, it is an inappropriate description, as Murphy is still alive.


