|}

{{BookCat}}

[[File:Ulysses, 1922.djvu|thumb|600px|center|page=588]]
<br>
==Annotations==
'''''minutiae'''''{{spaces|5}}''minor details''; ''trifles''. Like ''alias'' on the previous page, ''[[wikt:minutia|minutiae]]'' is a late borrowing from Latin, which has become a naturalized English expression and is not generally italicized;<ref>[http://www.etymonline.com/index.php?term=minutiae&allowed_in_frame=0 Online Etymology Dictionary.]</ref> but the narrator of this episode (Bloom?) italicizes every word that has been borrowed from a foreign language, whether naturalized or not.

