==Annotations==
'''''ad libitum'''''{{spaces|5}}(''Latin'') ''at one's pleasure''. In vocal music, this expression gives the singer licence to improvise; it is also used to indicate that a passage may be omitted in performance, though that is unlikely to be the meaning here, where the words are on the last page of the song.


